               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Sǝnkǝssar “Synaxarion” for the first half of the year (fols.
                     3ra-179rc) 
 I-1) Maskaram (fols. 3ra–35rc)
 I-2) Ṭǝqǝmt (fols.
                     36ra–56vc)
 I-3) Ḫǝdār (fols. 57ra–83vc)
 I-4) Tāḫśāś (fols.
                     84ra–119rb) 
 I-5) Ṭǝrr (fols. 119va–154vc)
 I-6) Yakkātit (fols.
                     155ra–179rc)
 The commemorative notices are followed by ʿarke-hymns
                     
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The concluding prayer Za-ʾaqrabku māḥleta… “The prayer I have offered…”
                        was started but left unfinished on <locus target="#119rb">119rb</locus>.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
